The paper focuses on analyzing the generalization properties of neural networks in gradient-based meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments involve image classification tasks (cs.CV) and natural language processing tasks (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the coherence between adaptation trajectories in parameter space, which is a concept related to neural network optimization (cs.NE).
